Research Projects


&lt;article class="project-card project-card-wide"&gt;
  &lt;div class="status-badge"&gt;Working Paper&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;Pre-move Publication-Location Exposure and Destination Choice among Elite Biomedical Scientists&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research question.&lt;/strong&gt; How is a scientist's pre-move publication-location exposure associated with observed destination choice among candidate cities?&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data.&lt;/strong&gt; Event-specific destination-choice data derived from elite biomedical scientist mobility records. Restricted source data are not public.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Methods.&lt;/strong&gt; Event-specific candidate sets, origin-anchored pre-move exposure measures, conditional logit models, candidate-set checks, and coverage diagnostics.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Current output or repository.&lt;/strong&gt; Working paper. Restricted source data and full manuscript materials are not publicly released here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/article&gt;

&lt;article class="project-card project-card-wide"&gt;
  &lt;div class="status-badge"&gt;Accepted&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;Spatial Structure and Determinants of Top Global Biomedical Scientists' Mobility from an Urban Network Perspective&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research question.&lt;/strong&gt; How can the mobility of top global biomedical scientists be described from an urban network perspective?&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data.&lt;/strong&gt; Scientist mobility and city-level network data assembled for the article. Public release is not available here.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Methods.&lt;/strong&gt; Urban network analysis and empirical analysis of spatial structure and associated determinants.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Current output or repository.&lt;/strong&gt; Accepted article. Final publication metadata will be added after confirmation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/article&gt;

&lt;article class="project-card project-card-wide"&gt;
  &lt;div class="status-badge"&gt;Master's Thesis&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;Intercity Mobility Network of Top Global Biomedical Scientists: A Dual Perspective of Whole and Ego Networks&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research question.&lt;/strong&gt; What patterns appear in the intercity mobility network of top global biomedical scientists from whole-network and ego-network perspectives?&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data.&lt;/strong&gt; Mobility records and city-level network data assembled for the master's thesis.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Methods.&lt;/strong&gt; Whole-network analysis, ego-network analysis, and spatial interpretation of mobility patterns.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Current output or repository.&lt;/strong&gt; Master's thesis completed at East China Normal University.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/article&gt;

&lt;article class="project-card project-card-wide"&gt;
  &lt;div class="status-badge"&gt;Ongoing Research&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;Global Mobility and Collaboration Networks of Elite Biomedical Scientists&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research question.&lt;/strong&gt; How are mobility, collaboration, institutions, and cities connected in longitudinal scientific career data?&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data.&lt;/strong&gt; Longitudinal scientist-institution-city data under construction. Raw data are not public.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Methods.&lt;/strong&gt; Directed weighted mobility networks, ego-network indicators, collaboration networks, and WERGM-based specifications.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Current output or repository.&lt;/strong&gt; Ongoing research extension of earlier thesis and article work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/article&gt;

&lt;article class="project-card"&gt;
  &lt;div class="status-badge"&gt;Public Repository&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;Author-Institution Linkage and Geocoding Feasibility Audit&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research question.&lt;/strong&gt; How can author-institution-city linkage and geocoding workflows be audited before restricted bibliographic data are used?&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data.&lt;/strong&gt; Fully synthetic demonstration records. The repository does not include real Scopus, OpenAlex, ROR, scientist, paper, or institution data.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Methods.&lt;/strong&gt; Schema validation, identifier linkage, institution normalization, city-country validation, QA checks, duplicate diagnostics, confidence diagnostics, and coverage reporting.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Current output or repository.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://github.com/Olivia-wr-research/author-institution-city-linkage"&gt;Public GitHub repository&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/article&gt;
